 Port Elizabeth - The Provincial Organized Crime Investigation Unit (Prov OCI) in Port Elizabeth is seeking assistance from the community for information leading to arrest of suspects involved in a break-in at a supermarket in Algoa Park. "It is alleged that on Friday, at 21:16, the store manager locked the shop in Algoa Park and activated the alarm," said police spokesperson, Capt Sandra Janse Van Rensburg. "On opening the shop on Saturday, at approximately 05:55, she once again deactivated the alarm. "It was at that time that she noticed that the ATM inside the store was forced opened and she immediately called the police. "The Bomb Disposal Unit was summoned to inspect the ATM, prior to any entry." Capt Janse van Rensburg said that the ATM was forced opened with an angle grinder and an unknown amount of suspects gained entry through the roof. "An unknown amount of cash was taken." The Provincial Organized Crime Investigation Unit is requesting anyone who may have information regarding this housebreaking to contact Lt Col Willie Mayi on 0826975914. All information will be treated with confidentiality. Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 